The Committee of the mosque is bringing up a Madarsa for the Islamic education of the children for which they are raising funds as well. The street in which this mosque is located, is a narrow one, hence no space for car entry or parking, however, two wheelers are parked near the mosque.

featured_reviews.review_id: The Moti Masjid (lit. 'Pearl mosque') is a white marble mosque inside the Red Fort complex in Delhi, India. Located to the west of the Hammam and close to the Diwan-i-Khas, it was built by the Mughal emperor Aurangzeb from 1659-1660. The mosque is plastered in white on the outside. The courtyard measures 40 x 35 feet.
